  <section xml:id="intro">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <para>RELAX NG is a schema language for XML. It is simpler than XML Schema
    (XSD) and more expressive than DTDs.</para>
    <para>Key features include:</para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para>Clean syntax in both XML and compact notation</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>Datatype support via external libraries</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para>Namespace awareness</para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>

  <section xml:id="usage">
    <title>Usage</title>
    <para>To validate an XML file against a schema, use the <command>jing</command>
    tool or a compatible validator.</para>

    <programlisting language="bash">jing schema.rng document.xml</programlisting>

    <note>
      <para>Exit code 0 means valid, exit code 1 means invalid.</para>
    </note>

    <section xml:id="datatypes">
      <title>Datatypes</title>
      <para>RELAX NG supports external datatype libraries. The most common is
      <literal>http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-datatypes</literal>.</para>
      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><code>xsd:integer</code></term>
          <listitem><para>Arbitrary-precision integer values.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><code>xsd:dateTime</code></term>
          <listitem><para>ISO 8601 date/time strings.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><code>xsd:anyURI</code></term>
          <listitem><para>Absolute or relative URI references.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section xml:id="conclusion">
    <title>Conclusion</title>
    <para>RELAX NG is an excellent choice for XML schema definition. Its
    simplicity and power make it suitable for a wide range of applications.</para>
    <blockquote>
      <attribution>James Clark</attribution>
      <para>The fundamental insight of RELAX NG is that validation is a
      derivative operation.</para>
    </blockquote>
  </section>
